            <h3 data-uuid="cf0e34d876b242a7b55eb2bcae7cd358">Part 2: Write a Compare and Contrast Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="6794fb3f141a441da6be6367ed58d0be">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="951a578699e24d21a0fbcdc61314663c">Beginning in the 1820s, the Mexican government invited
                Americans to settle in the sparsely populated territories along Mexicoâ€™s
                northern frontier. In return for land, Americans agreed to abide by Mexican
                laws and respect Mexican culture and religion. In time, the Mexicans and
                Americans living in these territories wanted independence and a bigger voice in
                their government. When revolts began in Texas and California, they
                were the result of Mexicans and Americans working together to gain greater
                freedom. After the wars ended and treaties were signed, gold was discovered in
                California, ushering in a new wave of migration from all over the world.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="97cbce38c1174417bf9e9b5ae9f11281">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="27e5d92963fe4307a1e4384dacf409e0">From Texas to California, settlers moved to
                unknown lands in search of a better life. Upon their arrival, settlers met with
                varying challenges and successes. They would also forever change the regions
                they moved into. Review the document-based investigation materials in Part 1. Write
                an essay in which you compare and contrast the challenges and opportunities for
                Mexicans, Americans, Chinese, and Native Americans in the Southwest during the
                1840s and 1850s.</p>
            <p data-uuid="77bf620cf681443c8f5f0de80037ef27">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="dc9454a62f1142a4b536628d552d8b7d">
                <li data-uuid="c4a6e49c53e94ba8bee97f9b23b65e50">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="e7da4b9ac8a7422899b9b180e4803aaa">
                    Use at least <i>two</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic
                    with relevant, well-chosen text evidence from the documents.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="62dec5fb30c64ddf9ea1ccae15c1c6ba">
                    Cite specific text evidence from each of the sources in your
                    response.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="511425aa4b424afaab0191d7f743c50d">
                    Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a conclusion.</li>
                <li data-uuid="6c8a2e4d727a4a01b22eb778d370dad0">Organize your essay in a clear and logical way that highlights
                    comparisons and contrasts.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="9f245f150be6410e94f3e6a487e2e5a3">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
